					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/11/27/eye/#comment-977">
							<time datetime="2010-12-08T13:12:16+00:00">
								December 8, 2010 at 1:12 pm							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I think I must agree with the guys on this one.  I think it was a bit stressed.  To me, the sentence &#8216;I can’t shake the feeling that it’s watching me, leering&#8217; in the beginning is enough to set the threat in mind.  And as you read, the threat will grow along with the girl&#8217;s fear.  </p>
<p>It could be that because I am a girl living in a city, the threat is already in my mind and so was an automatic assumption when I started reading.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

